The paper deals with creating strong agents for games, which is a common topic in the field of AI (cs.AI). The approach used is based on game-theoretic solution concepts such as Nash equilibrium, which falls under the category of game theory (cs.GT). The paper also discusses the success of the agent in defeating opponents, which is related to machine learning and reinforcement learning (cs.LG). The game being studied is a multiplayer game, which falls under the category of multi-agent systems (cs.MA). Finally, the paper deals with the strategy of the agent, which is related to decision-making and optimization (cs.SI).
